          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><hr />\n<h2 id=\"section-2-episode-trajectories-following-an-episode\">Section 2 \u00b7 Episode Trajectories \u2014 Following an Episode</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">RL is fundamentally <strong>sequential</strong>. The UMAP projection above treats each\ntransition as an independent point \u2014 losing the temporal structure.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Here we restore that structure: <strong>select an episode</strong> with the slider and see:</span>\n<ul>\n<li>Its <strong>path through the embedding</strong> (which regions of state-space the agent visited)</li>\n<li>A <strong>timeline</strong> showing how the pole angle and Q-value evolved step by step</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Try this:</strong> Compare an early episode (short, agent falls fast) with a late\nepisode (long, agent balances). Notice how late episodes trace extended paths\nthrough the \"safe\" region of the embedding.</span>\n</blockquote></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
